# Auto-build after build fix series

When you finish a **connected set of changes** that fix or materially affect **compilation, packaging, manifests, CI, or publish output** (or crash fixes that need a fresh binary to verify), do **not** end the turn until you have:

1. Run **`dotnet build -c Release`** on the solution (or the affected projects if scope is narrow and the user only touched one app).
2. If the work affects **runnable desktop behavior** (Avalonia/WPF, LibVLC, Live View, single-file publish, native hosts), also produce a **local smoke publish** the user can run immediately:
   - **Avalonia Windows x64:** publish `src/OnvifDeviceManager/OnvifDeviceManager.csproj` with `-c Release -r win-x64 --self-contained true -p:PublishSingleFile=true -p:PublishTrimmed=false -p:IncludeNativeLibrariesForSelfExtract=true` to **`publish/local-test/OnvifDeviceManager-Avalonia-win-x64`**, then run **`build/repair-win-apphost.ps1`** on that folder with `-ExeBaseName OnvifDeviceManager` (same flags as README preview flow).
3. In the reply, give the **full path** to the folder or `.exe` to run (no making the user hunt).

4. **Download / CI link (required):** Always include how to pull binaries without syncing the repo:
   - **Stable / tagged assets:** [Releases](https://github.com/devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM/releases) and, when README lists them, the verbatim `https://github.com/devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM/releases/download/...` rows for that tag — **never invent** `releases/download/...` URLs that are not on the release.
   - **Latest `main` CI (portable WPF + Avalonia ZIPs inside one artifact):** paste this workflow view (pick the newest successful run, then **Artifacts**):
     - [Build workflow — runs on `main`](https://github.com/devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM/actions/workflows/dotnet.yml?query=branch%3Amain)
   - After you **push** commits in the same fix series, run **`gh run list --repo devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM --workflow=dotnet.yml --branch=main --limit=1 --json url,conclusion,status,displayTitle`** (or equivalent) and paste the **verbatim run URL** so the user can open it directly. Artifact name pattern on that run: **`ONVIF-ODM-Windows-x64-r{run_number}-{run_attempt}`** (ZIP contains both `OnvifDeviceManager-*-win-x64-v{version}-{stamp}.zip` files). If the run is still **in progress**, say so and keep the workflow link above as the fallback.
   - **GitHub does not offer a stable permanent URL** to a given artifact ZIP without opening the run; the run URL + artifact name is the practical “download link.”

Do this **automatically**; do not wait for the user to say “build it again,” “so we can test it,” or “give me a download link.”

Full release ZIPs / `create-release-package.ps1` remain **only when** the user asks for a shipping drop or release SOP.
